Item 1.02 Termination of a Material Definitive Agreement.
On July 17, 2008, Allegiant Air, LLC, a wholly-owned subsidiary of Allegiant Travel Company (the "Company") received a notice of termination from MLT Vacations under which the Charter Services Agreement between the parties will be terminated effective as of October 20, 2008. Under the Agreement, Allegiant Air was to devote one aircraft to provide charter services for MLT Vacations from the end of May 2008 through the end of 2009, subject to earlier termination. MLT Vacations cited rising fuel prices and lack of fare improvements as reasons for the contract termination.
