Item 1.01 Entry into a Material Definitive Agreement.
On June 21, 2010, Allegiant Air, LLC, a wholly-owned subsidiary of Allegiant Travel Company (the "Company") entered into an amendment of its agreement with multiple Harrahs hotel properties in Las Vegas, Nevada. Under the amendment, the Company will pay Harrahs $25,000,000 in exchange for discounted room rates over the term of the agreement, which will expire no later than 30 months after payment. The Company is not required to purchase any amount of rooms under the agreement and the Harrahs entities are obligated to repay the unused portion of the prepayment upon the termination or expiration of the agreement. The agreement is not exclusive in nature and does not preclude the Company from developing additional strategic hotel partnerships.
