Item 2.03 Creation of a Direct Financial Obligation or an Obligation under an Off-Balance Sheet Arrangement of a Registrant.
On August 30, 2010, Allegiant Travel Company (the "Company"), through a wholly owned subsidiary, entered into a Loan Agreement with Wells Fargo Equipment Finance, Inc. under which it borrowed $14.0 million secured by two Boeing 757 aircraft. The notes evidencing the loan bear a fixed interest rate and will be amortized in monthly installments over 48 months. The Company has guaranteed the debt. A portion of the proceeds of the loan was applied to pay off debt of approximately $7.2 million secured by four MD-80 aircraft, which are now unencumbered.
