Section 2                      Financial Information
Item 2.03                      Creation of a Direct Financial Obligation or an Obligation under an Off-Balance Sheet Arrangement of a Registrant.
 
On September 27, 2011, a wholly-owned subsidiary of Allegiant Travel Company (the "Company") borrowed $7.0 million under the August 2010 Loan Agreement it had previously entered into with Wells Fargo Equipment Finance, Inc. The loan is secured by one of the Companys Boeing 757 aircraft. The note evidencing the loan bears interest at a fixed rate and will be amortized in monthly installments over 48 months.The Company has guaranteed the debt.
 
