Section 1              Registrants Business and Operations
 
Item 1.01               Entry into a Material Definitive Agreement.
 
As of May 20, 2013, Allegiant Travel Company (through a wholly owned subsidiary) (the Company) became bound by the terms of an Agreement of Sale and Purchase under which the Company has agreed to purchase approximately 10 acres of property in northwest Las Vegas on which there are located five office buildings containing approximately 130,000 square feet of currently vacant office space. The total price for the purchase will be approximately $12.3 million. The sellers of the property are Crossing Business Center 1 and 2 LLC and Crossing Business Center 7 LLC. The sellers have no prior relationship with the Company. The Company expects to close the purchase before the end of second quarter 2013 and expects to begin to move its corporate headquarters to the new facility after certain improvements to the space are completed.
 
 
 
 
